title: chapter1_openingScene
tags:
---
<<declare $playerName = "Player">>
<<declare $hatedFood = "Apple">>
<<declare $lovedFood = "Pie">>
<<declare $familiar = "Familiar">>
<<declare $chapter_1_prof_olivia_ask_repeat = 0>>
<<declare $George_Activated = 0>>
<<declare $Gigi_Activated = 0>>
<<decalre $Roy_Activated = 0>>
<<decalre $Sheila_Activated = 0>>
<<decalre $Damien_Activated = 0>>
<<decalre $Eliza_Activated = 0>>
<<declare $George_Affection = 0>>
<<declare $Gigi_Affection = 0>>
<<declare $Roy_Affection = 0>>
<<declare $Sheila_Affection = 0>>
<<declare $Matthias_Affection = 0>>
<<declare $Charlotte_Affection = 0>>
<<declare $Damien_Affection = 0>>
<<declare $Eliza_Affection = 0>>
<<declare $DamienElizaNowayIdontwanttogetcaughtupinthis = "">>
Narrator: Your dreams are fading fast. 
Narrator: This could be your only chance to escape the mundane future ahead of you. You steady the quill in your hand and complete the scholarship application.
Narrator: You sign your application and send it with the last post. Time comes and goes. 
Narrator: Your twentieth birthday passes. But you never hear back.
===

title: chapter1_dadIntro
tags:
position: -180,-527
---	
Dad: Morning {$playerName}, how are you feeling? Are you ready for your first day of work?
Player: ... 
Dad: Hey, I know you had your heart set on that scholarship. 
Dad: But working as a servant in the manor won't be all that bad. At least you won't have to work in the mines like I did.
    -> Player: Right... I get to watch Gigi and George become Adventurers while I sit at home and dust their silverware.
    -> Player: Yeah. I guess it could be worse.
Dad: I'm sorry {$playerName}. I know it's unfair only nobles get to become Adventurers. 
Dad: I would give you the money if we had it. But we can't even afford a Familiar for the house.
===

title: chatper1_dadBreakfast
tags:
---
Dad: Here. I made you a good, hearty breakfast. I want you to know that I love you and I'm very proud of you, no matter what.
    -> Player: ~ I can tell Dad put a lot of effort into this. I should finish it.
        Narrator: You think you spot Dad wiping away a tear.
    -> (Push the food around the plate.)
        Narrator: You think you hear Dad heave a forlorn sigh.
    -> Player: What the hell, Dad? You know I hate {$hatedFood}! Why can't you do anything right?
        Dad: Oh! I'm sorry. I was so focussed on making everything special. 
        Dad: Agh, everything was supposed to be perfect!
===

title: chapter1_dadIntro_2
tags:
---
Dad: Is that a letter?
Dad: It's for you, {$playerName}.
Dad: What is it?
===

title: chapter1_dadIntro_3
tags:
---
Player: It's a response to my scholarship application. And an apology for the delay. 
Player: I've... I've been accepted!
Dad: What? That's incredible! 
Dad: Ah! Erm... What do we do? 	
Dad: Okay. It's still very early in the day. We have time. 
Dad: Firstly, who is your sponsor?	
Player: Professor Olivia.
Dad: Phew! She's here in the village right now. 
Dad: Go to see her right away. I'll go to the manor and explain you won't be accepting the position as a servant.
    -> Player: Thanks, Dad.
    -> Player: Whatever. I'm out of here!
Dad: Meet me there to say goodbye before you leave, okay?
===
title:chapter1_BrackenberryVillage_ProfOlivia
tags:
position: 72,-525
---
Professor Olivia: {$playerName}, I'm glad you're here! I take it you got the news too?	
    -> Player: A Familiar delivered the letter just now!
    -> Player: Just in time! I almost ended up a servant at the twin's manor.
Professor Olivia: It was a surprise to me as well. 
Professor Olivia: I hadn't realised you'd applied. I could have helped you with your application.
    -> Player: There wasn't time. You were away when I decided to apply.
    -> Player: You're never here. 
Professor Olivia: I see. Well, let's get started. 
Professor Olivia: Are you excited to meet your Familiar? #cutehappy
    -> Player: I can't wait! 
        Professor Olivia: That's nice to hear.
    -> Player: I just can't wait to leave this place.
        Professor Olivia: ...
<<jump chapter1_profOliviaRelOpt1>>
===
title:chapter1_profOliviaRelOpt1
tags:
position: 73,-318
---
Professor Olivia: Until now, the twins were the only ones under my sponsorship. They collected their Familiars last night. 
Professor Olivia: Unfortunately, the best I can offer you is from a breeder surplus this season. I took them in the hope of finding them a good home. <<once>>
    -> Player: What would have happened to them otherwise?<<once>>
        Professor Olivia: They would have been dumped in the Wilds. But they're already teeming with dangerous Familiars left to turn feral. It just makes the problem worse.
        <<jump chapter1_profOliviaRelOpt1>>
    -> Player: I don't want some noble's leftovers!
        Professor Olivia: Well, this is your only option. You're lucky to even get a choice at such short notice.  
    -> Player: I don't care where they've come from. 
        Professor Olivia: Ha! That's the spirit! #cutehappy
    -> Player: I guess they'll have to do.
        Professor Olivia: Indeed.
Professor Olivia: Go ahead. Pick which one you want. I'll just be working in my study over there.
===

title: chapter1_profOliviaChooseFam
tags:
position: 326,-319
---
Professor Olivia: Are you sure this is the one you want?
    -> Player: Yes
        Professor Olivia: Excellent! #happy 
        <<jump chapter1_profOliviaConfirmChoice>>
    -> Player: I'm not sure...
        Professor Olivia: You can swap them out at the pen. Take your time. This is important.
===

title: chapter1_profOliviaConfirmChoice
tags:
position: 327,-80
---
Professor Olivia: Now you've chosen your Familiar, there's a few things in the Adventurer Scholarship that I'm obligated to remind you about. 
Professor Olivia: Adventurers are funded by the crown and hence, you will receive an increased allowance as you rise up the ranks by defeating Guild Masters and their Familiars across Gantoh. 
Professor Olivia: If you defeat them all, then King Albert will award you the Diamond amulet and you will become a member of the prestigious Royal Council. 
Professor Olivia: Now, your first rank is brass and with it, the first scholarship payment.
Professor Olivia: This amulet will allow you access into the Wilds between settlements beyond Powder Town, should you wish to pass through there on foot to train with your Familiar. 
Professor Olivia: Remember, the Wilds are dangerous. Your Familiar is your responsibility. You can heal it at Healing Churches if it gets injured but if it dies under your care, then your journey will end.
Player: Okay. Where should I go first?
<<jump chapter1_profOliviaWhereNext>>
===

title: chapter1_profOliviaWhereNext
tags:
position: 329,147
---
Professor Olivia: The first Guild Master you'll want to defeat is Matthias in Salt Mire City. You can take the train from Powder Town. 
Professor Olivia: Oh, and don't worry about money for accommodation while you're travelling. Inns across Gantoh will provide Familiar Adventurers with free rooms, as per royal decree.
Professor Olivia: Did you understand all of that?
    -> Player: Yep. I need to get the train to Salt Mire City.
        <<jump chapter1_profOliviaHelpResearch>>
    -> Player: Can I hear that last bit again?
        <<set $chapter_1_prof_olivia_ask_repeat += 1>>
        Professor Olivia: Come on, now. Pay attention. #angry <<if $chapter_1_prof_olivia_ask_repeat > 2 >>
        <<jump chapter1_profOliviaWhereNext>>
===

title: chapter1_profOliviaHelpResearch
tags:
position: 326,371
---
Professor Olivia: One more thing. Since you'll be travelling all over Gantoh…
Player: What is it?
Professor Olivia: Do you fancy helping me with a bit of research?
    -> Player: Sure. 
    -> Player: Huh? 
Professor Olivia: I'm looking for some ancient elven artefacts. In particular, stone tablets with writing engraved on them. You might find them scattered in various places around Gantoh. 
Professor Olivia: With three new Adventurers under me this season, I'll have to abandon my own expeditions for a while. I would very much appreciate it if you let me examine any you find. 
Professor Olivia: If you bring me an artefact, I'll even share some more details of my research with you.
    -> Player: Of course. That sounds really interesting. 
        Professor Olivia: I'm pleased you think the same. 
    -> Player: I guess I'll consider it.
        Professor Olivia: I understand not everyone is interested in history. Ah well, my offer still stands regardless.
Professor Olivia: That should be everything you need to know for now. 
Professor Olivia: Remember to check back in with me here regularly so I know you're safe. Good luck! #wink
===

title: chapter1_TwinChoiceandBattle
tags:
---
George: Stop right there!
Gigi: Ho ho! Well, well. What do we have here, George?
George: We seem to have a little mouse on our tail, Gigi. With a...
Gigi: Is that a Familiar?!
Player: I was accepted for a scholarship under Professor Olivia. I'm an Adventurer, just like you two.
    -> Player: Now please excuse me.
    -> Player: Now please get out of my way.
Gigi: You are not even remotely like us two. How dare you even compare us with threadbare, penniless vermin like you.
George: You were meant to be scrubbing our clothes and polishing our boots! 
George: I was rather looking forward to tormenting you for the rest of our lives. How could Father allow this?
Player: He had no choice. By the king's decree.
Gigi: Ugh! Shut up!
George: Even after all these years, you still seem to be in need of another lesson in proper etiquette. 
George: By the king's decree, it's about time you were punished and sent home.
George: And yet, I can't help but think we should show a little magnanimity, for the Familiar's sake at least.
Gigi: I know! Let them pick which one of us will teach them their lesson.
George: Excellent idea. We'll let you decide how you lose.
Player: Fine. Let's do this.
    -> (Challenge Gigi.)
        <<set $Gigi_Activated = 1>>
        Gigi: Hmph!
    -> (Challenge George.)
        <<set $George_Activated = 1>>
        George: Whatever.
===

title: chapter1_TwinChoiceandBattle_PlayerLoses
tags:
---
Gigi: Ho ho! Guess you're adventure really is over.
George: I knew you weren't strong enough. You'd best get back to the manor and start washing those dishes.
===

title: chapter1_TwinChoiceandBattle_PlayerWins
tags:
---
George: I can't believe it!
Gigi: W-what just happened?
===

title: chapter1_GeorgeBattle_PlayerWins
tags:
---
Gigi: You did not just lose to them, did you? They're a peasant! They have no money and a joke of an education. What kind of noble are you?
George: I-I just pretended to lose. I'm giving them a false confidence boost so it will hurt even more when we crush them later.
Gigi: Who are you trying to fool? Your commands were weak, your strategic thinking pathetic! I noticed these shortfalls before but now they're obvious.
George: But… everyone says I have a natural talent for magic!
Gigi: Hmph! They just say that to coddle your delicate ego. 
Gigi: It's a shame I have to have you clinging onto my skirts everywhere I go… 
Gigi: Or do I?
George: What are you saying?
Gigi: I've made up my mind, George. 
Gigi: I don't wish to be associated with someone as weak as you anymore. You'll just make me a laughing stock. 
Gigi: You can look forward to watching from the crowd as King Alfred makes me a Royal Council member. If you even make it to Avaelon, that is.
George: Gigi...
    -> Player: Are you alright?
        <<set $George_affection += 1>>
        George: Ha! Don't worry yourself, little mouse. I'm made of stronger stuff than the likes of you.
    -> Player: She's right. You really are weak.
        George: I'll show you! As of today, I officially declare you my enemy!
George: I'll make sure to beat you next time. I'll show you no more mercy.
Player: This is going to be really awkward when I beat you again.
George: Play out those fantasies in your mind all you want. You got lucky this time and you know it.
Player: Guess I'll see you in Salt Mire City.
George: You'd best start preparing now. Enjoy this little taste of freedom. 
George: I'll send you packing back to the manor soon enough.
===

title: chapter1_GigiBattle_PlayerWins
tags:
---
George: You lost? What even was that?!
Gigi: I must have had a momentary lapse of concentration.
George: You needed to focus for once in your life. This was important, Gigi! Now this filthy urchin will be following us all around the kingdom. 
Gigi: I... I tried...
George: Not hard enough! 
George: I've just about had it with you. I can't afford to have a loser dragging me down and bringing shame upon the family. 
George: I know, the little mouse can follow you around the kingdom instead.
Gigi: What? George?
George: I'm doing this on my own, Gigi. 
George: As the firstborn son and heir to the family, I don't have any real need for you anyway. 
George: You can look forward to watching from the crowd as King Alfred makes me a Royal Council member. If you even make it to Avaelon, that is.
Gigi: ...
    -> Player: Are you okay?
         <<set $Gigi_affection += 1>>
        Gigi: Of course I'm okay! I never asked for your concern, peasant!
    -> Player: He's right. You'll never make it on your own.
        Gigi: What do you know, peasant? No one asked for your opinion!
Gigi: I'll be fine. I've done plenty of things on my own before.
Player: Like what?
Gigi: Like... erm... 
Gigi: Things!
Player: Guess I'll see you in Salt Mire City.
Gigi: You'll not see me anywhere! Don't you dare even approach me. 
Gigi: Ugh! Gross!
===

title: chapter1_PowderTown_TrainStation
tags:
---
Town Guard Captain: I have an announcement. 
Town Guard Captain: I'm afraid that early this morning, we discovered that the Familiar that powers the Gantoh train has been stolen.
Town Guard Captain: As a result, the train will not be running for the foreseeable until the Familiar is found.
Town Guard Captain: Please accept our apologies for any inconvenience caused.
Townsfolk: Who did this?
Town Guard Captain: The StopIt! Militia has been identified as the culprit. We cannot answer any further questions on the matter until our investigation has been completed. 
Town Guard Captain: Thank you and apologies again.
Player: ~ Well, this is unexpected. I need to find another way to Salt Mire City.
===

title: chapter1_PowderTown_HealingChurch_Roy1
tags:
---
Roy: ...
Roy: Welcome to the Powder Town Healing Church...
Roy: How may I help you today?
    -> Player: Are you okay?
        Roy: Am I... okay?
        Roy: You know, you're the only person who's asked me that.
            -> Player: What's wrong?
                <<set $Roy_Affection += 2>>
                <<set $Roy_Activated = 1>>
