title: chapter1_PowderTown_Inn
tags:
---
Innkeeper: Hi there! Another new Adventurer, right?
    -> Player: Yep!
    -> Player: None of your business.
Innkeeper: I'm guessing you've heard of the bother with the trains?
<<if $chapter1_PowderTown_TrainStation == 1>> 
    Player: Yeah. Sounds like the StopIt! Militia have really out-done themselves. 
    Player: Do you know how I can get to Salt Mire City without the train?  
    Innkeeper: Hmmm... If you want to get there, you'll have to go on foot through the Wilds. 
    Innkeeper: That shouldn't be a problem for you with your Familiar, though, if you show your amulet to the guards at the gate. 
<<endif>>
<<if $chapter1_PowderTown_TrainStation == 0>> 
    Player: Huh?
    Innkeeper: You'd best go check it out for yourself.
<<endif>>
===

title: chapter1_PowderTown_PowderSaltMireWildsGate
tags:
---
Guard: Halt! 
Guard: It's not safe beyond these walls.
Guard: Oh! My apologies, Adventurer. You may pass through of course. 
Guard: Please make sure to fully prepare before entering these Wilds. 
Guard: The Familiars in this area might be milder than their cousins further North but they can still be pretty dangerous.
    -> Player: I'm ready.
    -> Player: On second thought, I'll come back later.
===

title: chapter1_Home_SpeaktoDad
tags:
---
Dad: Oh, Hi {$playerName}! 
Dad: I didn't expect to see you so soon.
    -> Player: I just wanted to check in.
        Dad: It's always nice to see you and {$familiar}. Stay as long as you like and rest up.
    -> Player: I'm not sure if this adventuring life is for me after all.
        Dad: Oh... 
        Dad: You know, if you want I can always ask the manor if they'll take you back as a servant?
            -> Player: Actually, I'll be fine. 
                Dad: Don't lose heart! I know this is difficult but I believe in you.
            -> Player: I think that will be for the best. This is too hard.
                Dad: Are you sure, {$playerName}?
                    -> Player: Yes, I'm sure.
                    -> Player: Actually, I'll be fine.
                        Dad: Don't lose heart! I know this is difficult but I believe in you.
===

title: chapter1_PowderSaltMireWilds_Timmy
tags:
---
Timmy: Hi, I'm Timmy. I've been looking for some fossils around here. 
Timmy: Where is it? I thought I saw something shiny.
Player: What's this?
Timmy: Hey, that's mine! Hand it over!
    -> Player: Finders keepers!
    -> Player: Woah, calm down a second!
Timmy: ARGGGGHHHHH!
===

title: chapter1_PowderSaltMireWilds_TimmyBattle_PlayerLoses
tags:
---
Timmy: Ha… ha… The fossil is mine! 
Timmy: Oh, wait. This isn't what I thought it was. 
Timmy: You don't look so good, buddy. You should probably go back to Powder Town and heal up. 
Timmy: I'm an Adventurer too, so we'll probably run into each other again. 
Player:
    -> Player: You're a psycho!
    -> Player: No hard feelings.
Timmy: I promise I'll buy you a drink next time we meet as an apology.
===

title: chapter1_PowderSaltMireWilds_TimmyBattle_PlayerWins
tags:
---
Timmy: I'm sorry, buddy. I got a bit carried away there. 
Timmy: You can have the rock. It's not what I thought it was anyway. 
    -> Player: Wow... Okay.
    -> Player: No hard feelings.
Timmy: I'm an Adventurer too, so we'll probably run into each other again. 
Timmy: I promise I'll buy you a drink next time we meet as an apology.
===

title: chapter1_PowderSaltMireWilds_Anne
tags:
---
Anne: Aha! You! Yes, you! 
Anne: I'm Anne, a merchant from Omen City. 
Anne: I'm currently in a bit of a pickle, as you can see. A mining cart seems to have fallen down the old mountain tracks and blocked the road. My Familiar can't get through. So we're a bit stuck. 
    -> Player: You need some help?
        Anne: I do indeed, my new Adventurer friend.
    -> Player: I fail to see how that's my problem.
        Anne: Oof! How very rude!
Anne: Look, there's a bargain to be had here for both of us. 
Anne: You want to get to Salt Mire City too, right? 
Anne: I'll help you out with some information. And then you can help me. Deal?
    -> Player: Sure.
        Anne: Fabulous! 
        Anne: There are tunnels through the mines from the entrance just west of here, behind some bushes. 
        Anne: You'll be able to pass through on foot but I can't leave my goods here unattended. 
        Anne: Can you go through the mines and look out for the switch to move the carts along the tracks? That should move this pesky thing!
        Anne: What do you think, brave Adventurer?
            -> Player: No problem. I'll look out for the switch.
                Anne: Thanks! See you later! 
                Anne: Oh, and be careful. There's been some tremors around here lately. 
                Anne: Who knows what's been going on in those old mines since they were abandoned. 
            -> Player: I don't have time for that.
                Anne: Seriously? 
                Anne: Well, you know my information now. I guess I'll just have to hope you change your mind.
    -> Player: No thanks. I'm not interested.
        Anne: Eh!? 
        Anne: Well then, I'll have to hope that someone more helpful comes along. 
        Anne: Thanks for nothing.
===

title: chapter1_GruntChoiceandBattle
tags:
---
StopIt! Militia Grunt 1: Ugh, it's so heavy! It won't budge.
StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: It seems to be in some sort of stasis. 
StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: It's probably easier for us if it doesn't wake up. 
StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: Maybe we can drag it out of here if we tie a rope around it and pull hard enough?
StopIt! Militia Grunt 1: As long as we can do this quickly and get out of here before anyone spots us.
StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: Ha! Why would anyone else be stupid enough to crawl through some abandoned mine tunnels?
Player: They're from the StopIt! Militia! I recognise their uniforms.
    -> Player: Stop right there!
    -> Player: Me, apparently.
    -> Player: ...
StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: Who are you?
StopIt! Militia Grunt 1: It doesn't matter who they are, Damien. 
StopIt! Militia Grunt1: Look, stranger. You'll just turn around and pretend you didn't see anything, if you know what's good for you.
    -> Player: I don't think so. 
        Player: You're trying to capture that wild Familiar, aren't you?
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 1: So what if we are? 
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 1: We're part of an unstoppable, mighty cause. You don't stand a chance against us
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: Especially since there's two of us and only one of you. 
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: Actually, they could run and tell the guards, Eliza. 
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: We'd better tie them up and leave them here.
    -> Player: Who are you to tell me what to do?
        Player: Get out of my way.
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 1: Pffft! How amusing. 
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 1: You really think you stand a chance against us?
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: They're pissing me off.
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: Eliza, they could spoil our mission too. 
        StopIt! Militia Grunt 2: We'd better tie them up and leave them here so they don't get in our way.
Eliza: You're right, Damien. Let's get 'em!
Damien: It's woken up!
Eliza: Shit! Get the rope!
Eliza: Agh! What is it doing?
Damien: It's caving in the tunnel! Run!
   -> (Follow Eliza.)
    <<set $Eliza_Activated = 1>>
        Eliza: That was close... 
        Eliza: Wait, what are you doing here? Where's Damien? 
        Eliza: Argh, this is all your fault! 
        Eliza: You should have turned around while you had the chance.
    -> (Follow Damien.)
        <<set $Damien_Activated = 1>>
        Damien: Tch! We nearly got buried alive back there...
        Damien: Wait, what are you doing here? Where's Eliza? 
        Damien: Ugh, this is bad. 
        Damien: I'd better stop you before you cause us any more trouble.
===

title: chapter1_ElizaBattle_PlayerLoses
tags:
---
Eliza: I warned you, stranger. 
Eliza: The StopIt! Militia will change this kingdom forever and you're all powerless to prevent it.
===

title: chapter1_ElizaBattle_PlayerWins
tags:
---
Eliza: No... We're an unstoppable force... 
Player: It looks like we're trapped down here. 
    -> Player: Come on, let's put our differences aside and see if we find a way out. 
        <<set $Eliza_Affection += 1>>
    -> Player: You can either help me or you can stay here and die alone.
Eliza: ...
Eliza: Fine. I'll come with you. 
Eliza: But don't get the wrong idea. This doesn't make us allies or anything.
Eliza: Well, this is awkward.
    -> Player: Tell me about it.
    -> Player: ...
Eliza: ...
Player: ...
Eliza: ...
Player: Why are you causing harm to all these Familiars?
Eliza: Harm? You are the ones causing harm!
Eliza: The StopIt! Militia has a noble cause. 
Eliza: It wants to free these creatures from human slavery. 
Eliza: Have you ever stopped to think if owning and controlling Familiars is in everyone's best interests?
    -> Player: Many people love and care for their Familiars. 
        <<set $Eliza_Affection += 1>>
        Eliza: And what about the people that don't?
    -> Player: Not really. But it's just how the world is.
        Eliza: Tch! How blind and shallow you must be. 
Eliza: They're dangerous weapons. No one should be controlling them.
Player: You're kidnapping them and hurting people. That's not okay. 
Player: Besides, you have your own Familiar right there! 
Player: How can your organisation judge others if you aren't living by the standards you're preaching?
Eliza: Whatever. You're an Adventurer. 
Eliza: Of course someone like you doesn't get it.
Player: ...
Eliza: ...
Player: I think I see an exit just up ahead.
Eliza: ...
Eliza: Damien!
Damien: Eliza! 
Damien: What's that stranger doing with you?
Eliza: Don't worry about it. Let's just get out of here.
===

title: chapter1_DamienBattle_PlayerLoses
tags:
---
Damien: You bit off more than you could chew, didn't you? 
Damien: Well, this is just a taste of what's to come. 
Damien: The StopIt! Militia will change this kingdom forever and you're all powerless to prevent it.
===

title: chapter1_DamienBattle_PlayerWins
tags:
---
Damien: What? No! 
Damien: This can't be happening...
Player: It looks like we're trapped down here. 
    -> Player: Come on, let's put our differences aside and see if we find a way out. 
        <<set $Damien_Affection += 1>>
    -> Player: You can either help me or you can stay here and die alone.
Damien: ...
Damien: Fine. I'll come with you. 
Damien: But don't get the wrong idea. This doesn't make us friends or anything.
Damien: Well, this is awkward.
    -> Player: Yep.
    -> Player: ...
Damien: ...
Player: ...
Damien: ...
Player: Why are you causing harm to all these Familiars?
Damien: Harm? You are the ones causing harm!
Damien: The StopIt! Militia has a noble cause. 
Damien: It wants to free these creatures from human slavery. 
Damien: Have you ever stopped to think if owning and controlling Familiars is what they want?
    -> Player: Many Familiars love and care for their masters. 
        <<set $Damien_Affection += 1>>
        Damien: And what about the masters who mistreat them?
    -> Player: Not really. But it's just how the world is.
        Damien: Tch! That's just the kind of response I expected from someone like you. 
Damien: They're sentient beings. No one should be controlling them.
Player: You're kidnapping them and hurting people. That's not okay. 
Player: Besides, you have your own Familiar right there! 
Player: How can your organisation judge others if you aren't living by the standards you're preaching?
Damien: Whatever. You're an Adventurer. 
Damien: Of course someone like you doesn't get it.
Player: ...
Damien: ...
Player: I think I see an exit just up ahead.
Damien: ...
Damien: Eliza!
Eliza: Damien!
Eliza: What's that stranger doing with you?
Damien: They'll not cause us anymore trouble. Let's just get out of here.
===

title: elvenrelic1_ProfOliviasHouse
tags:
---
Professor Olivia: Hi {$playerName}. Good to see you. 
Professor Olivia: What can I do for you?
    -> Player: Nothing in particular.
        Professor Olivia: You and your Familiar both look well. Keep up the hard work.
    -> Player: I found one of those elven relics you mentioned.
        Professor Olivia: Let me see!
        Professor Oliva: Excellent. This really is an elven relic. 
        Professor Olivia: The script engraved into the stone is a well-preserved example of their written language
        Player: Written Language?
        Professor Olivia: Indeed! 
        Professor Olivia: I'll let you in on a little secret. The current focus of my research is creating a codex of ancient elvish.
            -> Player: That's fascinating!
            -> Player: Why?
            Professor Olivia: If you can collect enough of these elven relics for me, then I will finally be able to fully translate Elvish into our tongue. 
            Professor Olivia: Think of the discoveries that could lead to! It can finally be spoken for the first time in hundreds of years!
            Player: I don't really know much about elves, except that they were cruel and evil and they're now extinct.
            Professor Oliva: Cruel and evil? 
            Professor Olivia: Yes, of course. The elves tried to enslave us, so humanity rose up and defeated them in a brave, righteous war.
            Player: That's right.
            Professor Olivia: ...
            Professor Olivia: {$playerName}, are you interested in continuing to help me out with my research
                -> Player: Definitely. I want to learn more about the elves.
                    Professor Oliva: You show a lot of promise, {$playerName}! 
                    Professor Olivia: Ah, I don't wish to overwhelm you. Bring me another relic and we can take it from there.
                -> Player: Definitely. I want to help you.
                    Professor Olivia: That's very kind of you, {$playerName}. Bring me another relic and we can take it from there.
                -> Player: Not really. I'm content as I am.
                    Professor Oliva: An interesting perspective. 
                    Professor Olivia: If you change your mind, bring me another relic and we can take it from there.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_SSSpamTicketSeller
tags:
---
<<if $chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerWins == 0>> 
    Player: Hi, can I have a single ticket please?
    Ticket Seller: Ah, my apologies. 
    Ticket Seller: With the Gantoh train being out of service, I'm afraid tickets for the next voyage are all sold out. 
    Player: What!? Sold out?
    Ticket Seller: Wait, I can see you have an adventurer's amulet. 
    Ticket Seller: There are still a few golden tickets to be won.
    Player: What's a golden ticket?
    Ticket Seller: Oh, it's an excellent prize. 
    Ticket Seller: Not only will it get you a place on this voyage but you'll also get to dine at the Captain's table. A very prestigious prize indeed!
    Player: How do I win one?
    Ticket Seller: By beating the Salt Mire City Guild Master, Matthias. 
    Ticket Seller: I hear he's pretty tough... and handsome.
        -> Player: Okay... Thanks for the information. I'll be heading to the Guild Hall anyway.
        -> Player: Whatever. Thanks I guess.
    Ticket Seller: Goodbye and thank you for your custom!
<<endif>>
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_HealingChurch_Roy
tags:
---
Roy: Oh! Hi {$playerName}. Let me heal your Familiar up for you.
Player: Roy? What are you doing here?
Roy: Oh...
Roy: After speaking to you back in Powder Town, I decided to pack up and try to pursue my dream after all. 
Roy: I'm staying with my cousin Sheila who works at the Familiar Nursery here.
    -> Player: That's amazing! 
    -> Player: This is your dream?
Roy: Well, it's the first step anyway. 
Roy: One day, I want to become a Bishop and open my own Healing Church. 
Roy: I'm not a noble and don't have much money. So to do that, I'd have to get letters of recommendation from the Healing Churches across Gantoh. 
Roy: I managed to pluck up the courage to get one from Powder Town and head here. 
Roy: I even bought a golden ticket to Omen City on the SS Spam but...
    -> Player: You can do it, Roy!
        <<set $Roy_Affection += 1>>
        Roy: Y-you really think so?
            -> Player: For sure. I've never seen someone heal Familiars as good as you.
                Roy: You're really kind, {$playerName}. I-
                Healers: *whispering*
                Roy: ...
                Player: What are they gossiping about?
                Roy: ...
                Roy: You should probably go... 
                Roy: I'll see you in Omen City, right?
                <<if $chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerWins == 0>> 
                    Player: I'll see you on the SS Spam if I can get a ticket.
                <<endif>>  
                <<if $chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerWins == 1>> 
                    Player: I have a ticket for the SS Spam too. I'll see you there!
                <<endif>>  
                Roy: That's great! 
                Healers: *whispering*
                Roy: ...
                Roy: I don't feel so good...
                Player: Roy? Are you alright?
                Roy: Bye, {$playerName}. I'll see you soon.
            -> Player: Maybe you aren't cut out for this.
                Roy: Yeah... you're probably right. I just thought...
                Healers: *whispering*
                Roy: ...
                Roy: I don't feel so good...
    -> Player: That's a stupid dream. 
        Player: I'm not sure why you're bothering with something like that.
        Roy: Do you really think so? 
        Healers: *whispering*
        Roy: ...
        Roy: I don't feel so good...
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_FamiliarNursery_Sheila1
tags:
---
Sheila: Ugh... 
Sheila: No, Mab... 
Sheila: Don't nibble Lady Lucaria's fingers...
Player: Erm... Hello?
Sheila: Gah! 
Sheila: Sheila at Salt Mire City Familiar Nursery at your service! What kind of Familiar are you after today?
Player: Were you sleeping?
Sheila: Don't tell the Head Breeder, please! 
Sheila: To tell you the truth, I'm bored stiff here. 
Sheila: People around here only want Familiars for industry or housework... pulling carts, helping with fishing, tending to crops. 
Sheila: No one is remotely interested in how they look!
Player: How they look?
Sheila: Yes! You know, like whether they have signs of good breeding. I mean...
Sheila: Wait. What's your name again?
Player: {$playerName}.
Sheila: {$playerName}, see my Queen Mab here? What do you think of her?
    -> Player: She's cute!
        <<set $Sheila_Affection += 1>>
        Sheila: Exactly! Can you imagine her getting dirty doing manual labour? 
        Sheila: She's the result of all my hard work here... Err, in my free time, of course...
    -> Player: She doesn't look very industrious.
        Sheila: I should hope not! 
        Sheila: It took me years to breed one as fine as she. 
        Sheila: And what recognition does she get in a place like this? None!
Sheila: She could even win Crusts, I tell you!
Player: Crusts?
Sheila: The annual Familiar beauty contest in the Capital, Avaelon. 
Sheila: The first qualifier contest is in a few days in Omen City. 
<<if $Roy_Activated == 1>> 
    Sheila: My cousin, Roy, recently came to visit and bought a ticket for the SS Spam. 
    Sheila: He said he'd met someone who had inspired him to follow his dreams. 
    Sheila: I got all caught up in it and agreed to go with him. 
<<endif>>  
<<if $Roy_Activated == 0>> 
    Sheila: I got myself all worked up and bought a ticket for the SS Spam.
<<endif>>  
Sheila: I even spent most of my savings on upgrading my ticket for the SS Spam when I heard Lady Lucaria was going to be on the ship. But now I'm having second thoughts...
Sheila: What do you think I should do?
    -> Player: You should go. You and Queen Mab have got this!
        <<set $Sheila_Affection += 2>>
        <<set $Sheila_Activated = 1>>
        Sheila: You're right! We can do this! 
        Sheila: Thanks {$playerName}.
    -> Player: I think you should sell your ticket before you embarrass yourself.
        Sheila: ...
        Sheila: Sorry, Mab. I think I made a mistake.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_FamiliarNursery_Sheila2
tags:
