title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Timmy2
tags:
---
-> (Drink with Timmy.)
    Timmy: Here you go! Hands drink.
    Timmy: I realised I'd never asked your name.
    Player: Oh, I'm {$playerName}.
    Timmy: I have an interesting question for you {$playerName}, now that we've patched things over. 
    Timmy: How do you feel about bug-like Familiars?
        -> Player: It depends. They can be cute or creepy.
            Timmy: HA! You're right, there! 
            Timmy: That's why I love them so much. 
            Timmy: When I got a bit over-excited over that rock, I thought I might have found a fossil of one.
            Timmy: Fossils are easier to keep stashed in my pockets than live Familiars. HA! HA!
            Player: Yeah, I get that. 
            Player: Fossils must be hard to find, though? 
            Player: I don't think I've ever seen one.
            Timmy: Well, the Wilds are the best place to look. 
            Timmy: I haven't had much success yet but I hear a few have been found in the Omen Arrowroot Wilds recently. 
            Timmy: I'm headed there next. 
            Timmy: I'm after one fossil in particular. A really rare one! 
            Timmy: So if you hear of any other good fossil spots, then let me know, buddy!
            Player: Sure, I'll let you know, Timmy. 
            Player: See you later!
        -> Player: I want to squish them.
            Timmy: AGH! How could you say that? They're the best! 
            Timmy: Well, look here, buddy. 
            Timmy: I'm looking for some fossils of them in the Wilds. You can't squish fossils...
            Timmy: I'm heading to the Omen Arrowroot Wilds next to search there. 
            Timmy: I'm after one fossil in particular. A really rare one! 
            Timmy: So if you hear of any other good spots, then let me know, buddy!
            Player: Okay. If you insist, Timmy.
-> (Walk away.)
    Timmy: Hey! No hard feelings, right? 
    Timmy: At least let me know your name?
    Player: It's {$playerName}. 
    Player: You can keep your drink, Timmy.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_GuildHall
tags:
---
Clerk: Greetings, Adventurer! 
Clerk: This is your first time in a Guild Hall, right? 
Player: How did you know?
Clerk: You can always tell. 
Clerk: The innocent, lost aura... The bright glint in their eyes...
Clerk: Anyway, this is where you can challenge the Guild Master and their acolytes. 
Clerk: You have to beat the acolytes first before you can take on Matthias. 
Clerk: This Guild Hall is all about the water element.
Clerk: The other thing you can do here is collect your allowance from the King. 
Clerk: This is for subduing wild Familiars and keeping the Gantoh Kingdom safe. 
Clerk: The higher your amulet rank, the more money you get. 
Clerk: You can check out the rates on the notice board over there.
Clerk: So, what would you like to do today?
    -> Player: Take on the Salt Mire City Guild Master, Matthias.
        Clerk: Okay. You can proceed through the door up ahead when you're ready. 
        Clerk: Good luck! 
    -> Player: Collect my allowance.
         <<if $PlayerMoney == 0>> 
            Clerk: Looks like you haven't earned any money yet. 
            Clerk: Best get out there and subdue some wild Familiars.
         <<endif>>
        <<if $PlayerMoney > 0>> 
            Clerk: No problem. Here you go.
        <<endif>>
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias
tags:
---
Matthias: Hi, there! 
Matthias: I'm Matthias, the Guild Hall leader here. 
Matthias: Have you come to challenge me?
Player: Yes. I'm {$playerName}, from Brackenberry Village. 
Player: Professor Olivia is my sponsor.
Matthias: Professor Olivia? 
Matthias: That's the third time I've heard that name recently. 
Matthias: The other two were pretty strong, so I have high hopes for you, {$playerName}!
Matthias: If you can defeat me, then you'll move up from brass to copper rank. 
Matthias: But I'm getting ahead of myself. 
Matthias: Come. Let's see what you can do.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerLoses
tags:
---
Matthias: Don't give up yet! 
Matthias: I saw signs of potential in you. 
Matthias: Promise me you'll come back for another try when you're ready?
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerWins
tags:
---
Matthias: Just as I thought! 
Matthias: The bond between you and your Familiar is strong already. Unusually so. 
Matthias: Yes, I have faith that you will go far in your Adventuring journey, {$playerName}. 
Matthias: Congratulations on reaching Copper Rank!
Player: Thank you. 
Player: What about the golden tickets for the SS Spam? I heard you were giving some away.
Matthias: You're in luck. I have one last golden ticket here. 
Matthias: The ship is leaving for Omen City tomorrow morning. 
Matthias: I'll actually be travelling on the boat too!
    -> Player: You're leaving Salt Mire City?
    -> Player: Oh... Why?
Matthias: I have something I need to sort out. 
Matthias: It's something I should have really done some time ago but it cannot wait any longer. 
Matthias: It's partly in my capacity as a Guild Master and Royal Council Member. 
Player: What's the other part?
Matthias: ...
Matthias: Do you believe in legends, {$playerName}?
    -> Player: Of course!
        <<set $Matthias_Affection = 1>>
        Matthias: I had a good feeling about you the moment you stepped into this room! 
        Matthias: Look for me when you're in Omen City. I have something interesting I'd like to show you.
    -> Player: They're nothing more than fairytales. 
        Matthias: Hmmm... That's disappointing to hear. 
        Matthias: Remember, all fairytales come from something. 
        Matthias: If you change your mind, seek me out in Omen City and we can continue this discussion.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Kenny1
tags:
---
Guard: So what did you see, ma'am?
Old Woman: Chaffy and I were just sitting in our usual spot, people watching in the town square, when we saw someone lurking.
Guard: Lurking?
Old Woman: Yes, lurking! 
Old Woman: They were very suspicious-looking. 
Guard: Do you have any details that might identify them?
Old Woman: Oh, my memory isn't what it used to be, sonny! 
Old Woman: They were kind of tall... I think? 
Old Woman: Or were they short? 
Old Woman: Maybe average-height?
Guard: Never mind. 
Guard: I'll see what I can do with your... information. 
Guard: Do you have anything to add to this report or are you simply eavesdropping?
    -> Player: Erm, no. Sorry. I was just curious.
    -> Player: Nothing at all.
Guard: Then be on your way, Adventurer. This is official business.
Old Woman: Hey, sonny. What's your name?
Guard: Kenny. 
Guard: Kenny, ma'am.
Old Woman: You look different to the usual city guards. 
Old Woman: Where do you come from?
Kenny: I must be on my way. 
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Anne
tags:
---
Player: Anne?
<<if $Agreed_Help_Anne == 1 and $Pulled_Lever == 1>>
    Anne: Hi, {$playerName}! Good to see you made it. 
    Anne: Thanks for helping me back there. 
    Anne: I was hoping we would meet again. I always believe you should always treat your investors well.
    Player: Investors?
    Anne: A good deed is an investment in another person, is it not? 
    Anne: I'd like to offer you a permanent discount on all my stock. 
    Anne: You'll not find bargains like this anywhere else!
        -> Player: Wow, thanks!
            Anne: No problem. 
        -> Player: Oh, okay.
            Anne: A little bit of an underwhelming response there, {$playerName}. 
        Anne: Anyway, feel free to have a look at my cart and see if there's anything you like.
<<endif>>
<<if $Agreed_Help_Anne == 0 and $Pulled_Lever == 1>>
    Anne: Hi, {$playerName}. Fancy seeing you around here. 
    Anne: I'm glad you changed your mind and decided to help me after all. 
    Anne: I was hoping we would meet again. I always believe you should always reward good business sense.
    Player: Business sense?
    Anne: You know, natural instincts that seek out good deals and fortuitous exchanges? 
    Anne: For pulling that lever, I'd like to give you a free healing potion.
        -> Player: Wow, thanks!
            Anne: No problem. 
        -> Player: Oh, okay.
            Anne: Don't look a gift horse... or potion... in the mouth, {$playerName}. 
    Anne: Anyway, feel free to have a look at my cart and see if there's anything you like.
<<endif>>
<<if $Agreed_Help_Anne == 0 and $Pulled_Lever == 0>>
    Anne: You!
    Anne: Bet you didn't expect to see me here after leaving me to fend for myself in the Wilds, did you? 
    Anne: I lost a good portion of my stock trying to move that mining cart out of the way.
        -> Player: I'm really sorry. I shouldn't have done that.
            Anne: No, you shouldn't. 
            Anne: But... I can probably forgive you, if you become a regular customer of mine.
        -> Player: I'd do it again. It was funny.
            Anne: You're a proper piece of work, aren't you?
    Anne: Well… You can still take a look at my cart and see if there's anything you like.
===

