title: chapter2_SSSpam_Intro
tags:
---
Butler: You seem a bit... different to our usual clientele. 
Butler: May I ask where you are from?
    -> Player: Brackenberry Village.
    -> Player: Nope.
Butler: I see...
Butler: It's clearly your first time aboard a luxury vessel. 
Butler: Well, you should feel privileged to have some very esteemed neighbours. 
Butler: A noble from the Sullivan family is residing in the cabin next door. One of the twins I do believe. 
Butler: This is your cabin. 
Butler: As a Golden Ticket holder, you have some free time to wander about before the bell rings for lunch at the Captain' table. 
Butler: Make sure you come back here to spruce yourself up beforehand. 
Butler: You don't want to make everyone feel uncomfortable, especially since it must have cost you dearly to purchase such a ticket.
Butler: Enjoy.
Player: Wow… I hate to admit it, but this is really nice. 
Player: I wonder how much this cabin would have normally cost?
Player: That snooty butler said I had some time to explore before lunch. I should make the most of it.
