---
Player: Matthias?
Matthias: Hey, {$playerName}! 
Matthias: How are your sea legs? 
Matthias: You seem to be faring better than poor Anne over there.
    -> Player: I'm barely noticing the waves. This ship sails so smoothly.
        <<set $Matthias_Affection += 1>>
        Matthias: Haha, you're a natural! 
        Matthias: You look almost as excited to be here as Nixie.
    -> Player: I can't wait to be on dry land.
        Matthias: Not long to go now! 
        Matthias: Poor Nixie will be devastated. She's having so much fun being out at sea.
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_Crew
tags:
---
SS Spam Crew 1: Do you not think our Familiars seem suddenly uneasy?
SS Spam Crew 2: For sure. One of them in the Engine Room was shaking all over and was refusing to come out to work.
SS Spam Crew 3: The cargo at the port back there was unusually heavy too. 
SS Spam Crew 3: What did the folks up in Management order this time?
SS Spam Crew 2: It doesn't help that the new hires we picked up in Salt Mire City are useless, not to mention unfriendly. 
SS Spam Crew 1: Ugh. Screw 'em all, I say. 
SS Spam Crew 1: Sometimes I even wonder if we're paid enough for this job.
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_CaptainsTable
tags:
---
Captain Drake: ... So, I think in total I've spent around ten years as Captain of this ship.
Captain Drake: They've flown by, with us sailing all over Gantoh. Haven't they, Lichen?
Lichen: Hop! Hop!
Captain Drake: Now, that's enough about me. 
Captain Drake: Where are you all from?
<<if $Roy_Activated == 1>> 
    Roy: Erm...
<<endif>>
Matthias: I'm from Salt Mire City.
<<if $Sheila_Activated == 1>>
    Sheila: Me too!
<<endif>>
<<if $George_Activated == 1>>
    George: I'm from near Powder Town. 
    George: Our family's estate covers vast swathes of the surrounding countryside. 
<<endif>>
<<if $Gigi_Activated == 1>>
    Gigi: I'm from near Powder Town. 
    Gigi: Our family's estate covers vast swathes of the surrounding countryside. 
<<endif>>
<<if $George_Activated == 1>>
    -> Player: I'm from Brackenberry Village. Same as George.
        <<set $George_Affection += 1>>
        George: ...
    -> Player: I'm from a small village called Brackenberry.
<<endif>>
<<if $Gigi_Activated == 1>>
    -> Player: I'm from Brackenberry Village. Same as Gigi.
        <<set $Gigi_Affection += 1>>
        Gigi: ...
    -> Player: I'm from a small village called Brackenberry.
<<endif>>
Captain Drake: Ah, so it sounds like you're all from a similar part of Gantoh. 
<<if $Damien_Activated == 1>> 
    Damien: The soup course will be some time, Sir. 
    Damien: I believe there have been some delays in the kitchen.
    Player: ...?
    Damien: Excuse me.
<<endif>>
<<if $Eliza_Activated == 1>>
    Eliza: The soup course will be some time, Sir. 
    Eliza: I believe there have been some delays in the kitchen.
    Player: ...?
    Eliza: Excuse me.
<<endif>>
Captain Drake: Ah, no matter. 
Captain Drake: Why don't you all take some time to get to know each other while we wait?
<<if $Damien_Activated == 1>> 
    Player: I feel like I've seen that waiter before somewhere...
<<endif>>
<<if $Eliza_Activated == 1>>
    Player: I feel like I've seen that waitress before somewhere...
<<endif>>
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_CaptainsTable_Matthias1
tags:
---
Matthias: The Captain is a really interesting guy but this formal dinner is a bit stuffy, isn't it? 
Matthias: Hey, have you heard of the Undersea Viewing Window down at the bottom of the ship? 
Matthias: I was speaking to the Captain and he said we could go and take a look with him if we wanted. 
Matthias: Let me know if you're interested. 
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_CaptainsTable_Matthias2
tags:
---
Matthias: So, do you want to come with me to see the Undersea Viewing Window?
    -> Player: Sure.
        Matthias: Great! Let's get out of here.
    -> Player: I'm not sure yet.
        Matthias: No worries. Just let me know if you're interested.
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_CaptainsTable_George1
