title: chapter2_SSSpam_Date_Matthias
tags:
---
Captain Drake: This is the Undersea Window. 
Captain Drake: The nobles book up for weeks for a chance for a private viewing but we had a cancellation last minute. 
Captain Drake: I'll leave you two to it. Enjoy and keep an eye out for any interesting Familiars! 
Captain Drake: I'll just be over at the back with Lichen if you need me.
Matthias: Wow! This is really impressive. 
Matthias: The ocean here really is beautiful. 
Matthias: What do you think of it, {$playerName}?
    -> Player: This is the first time I've seen the sea, nevermind below the sea!
        Matthias: I'm really glad we could share this moment together. 
        Matthias: I forget how vast and unexplored the waters in Gantoh are. 
        Matthias: Who knows what lurks within the mysterious corners of our Kingdom.
            -> Player: It's exciting.
                <<set $Matthias_Affection += 1>>
                Matthias: You think so? Ha ha! 
                Matthias: You definitely have an Adventurer's spirit, {$playerName}.
            -> Player: It's scary.
                <<set $Matthias_Affection += 2>>
                Matthias: ...
                Matthias: You know, there's a part of me that agrees with you.
        Matthias: Woah, did you see that? 
        Player: It's gone that way! 
        Matthias: Ah! Where? 
        Player: There! 
        Player: Wait, now it's there! 
        Player: Oh, that's actually a rock. Ha ha!
        Matthias: Ha ha! This is a lot of fun.
        Matthias: ...
        Matthias: {$playerName}, you know what?
        Player: Hmm?
        Matthias: I think this is the first time I've genuinely laughed in a long time. 
        Matthias: Ah! Ignore what I just said. I didn't mean to spoil the mood.
        Player: You didn't-
        Matthias: I meant to say, thanks for coming with me.
        Player: Thanks for inviting me.
        Matthias: I hope I'll get to see you again in Omen City. 
        Matthias: We'd better head back for now or we'll miss that soup course!
    -> Player: It's boring. I'm not really into water-type stuff.
        <<set $Matthias_Affection -= 1>>
        Matthias: Oh...
        Matthias: I mean, yeah it kind of is boring, isn't it? 
        Matthias: Sorry for dragging you all the way down here with me. 
        Matthias: I hope you'll still want to seek me out in Omen City. No hard feelings if not. 
        Matthias: For now, we'd better head back or we'll miss that soup course!
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_Date_George
tags:
---
George: And this is the Dance Hall. 
George: Many nobles come here for entertainment, obviously. 
George: We'd better not get any closer or they'll think we want to join in. 
George: I'm sure that would be pretty embarrassing for you, since you wouldn't know any of the steps.
Player: I know the steps.
George: You have to be joking? 
George: Where did someone like you learn dance steps like those?
Player: My Dad taught me. 
Player: Us poor people do sometimes pick up some things from being around you nobles, you know.
George: Pfft, a likely story. 
Player: I'm telling the truth, George. 
Player: In fact, I probably know those steps better than you.
George: As if! 
George: Wait… I have an idea. 
George: I'll give you one last chance to retract that outrageous statement.
George: Or are you willing to prove it, little mouse?
    -> Player: You first, my Lord.
        George: W-what? Are you sure? 
        George: Well, I suppose it will be hilarious to watch you fall on your face.
        George: ...
        George: I can't believe it... You're actually good?
        Player: Thanks for the compliment.
        George: That wasn't a... Ugh! You're so irritating. 
        George: Let's see if you can keep up with me if I pull out the even more advanced version of this dance!
            -> Player: (Perform the steps flawlessy, just like Dad taught you.)
                <<set $George_Affection += 1>>
                George: This must be some sort of twisted nightmare. 
                George: Even Gigi doesn't dance this well!
            -> Player: (Stamp on his foot.)
                <<set $George_Affection += 2>>
                George: Ouch! 
                George: What was that for?
        George: Right, see if you can handle this spin! 
        Player: Ooof!
        George: Agh!
        Player: Erm... We're a bit close...
        George: Ugh, you're right! 
        George: You should be grateful that I caught you after you tripped.
        Player: You were the one who tripped! 
        Player: You would've fallen if you hadn't grabbed onto me.
        George: In your dreams.
        George: Looks like the dance is over. 
        George: That was kind of fun. 
        George: Er, I mean, funny watching you try to compete!
        George: ...
        George: Let's head back before your stupid tour makes me miss the next course.
    -> Player: On second thought, maybe I don't actually know the steps that well.
        <<set $George_Affection -= 1>>
        George: Ha! I thought so. 
        George: Let's head back before your little tour makes me miss the next course.
===

