title: chapter2_SSSpam_Date_Roy
tags:
---
Roy: Sorry for dragging you away, {$playerName}. 
Roy: I never used to be this shy around people. 
Roy: I wish I was as brave as you. 
Roy: You weren't even intimidated by that mean noble.
Player: It wasn't always like that. 
Player: They used to pick on me a lot when I was younger. 
Player: It took me a lot of courage to finally stand up to them.
???: Luxo? Luxo, are you alright?!
Roy: That person sounds like they're in trouble! 
Roy: We should go and check on them!
    -> Player: Let's go!
        Roy: Okay, follow me!
        Roy: Hello? Is everything alright?
        ???: Oh, thank the Elements! 
        ???: Can you help us? 
        ???: My poor Familiar, Luxo, has taken a funny turn and isn't looking right at all.
        Roy: Don't worry! I'm from the Healing Church. 
        Roy: Let's take a look at you.
        Player: Luxo? 
        Player: You're Lady Lucaria, aren't you?
        Lady Lucaria: That's right. 
        Lady Lucaria: It's a pleasure to meet you both. 
        Lady Lucaria: I'm not sure where my servants have gone... 
        Roy: Hmm... When did this start?
        Lady Lucaria: He hasn't been right ever since he set foot on this ship. 
        Lady Lucaria: Oh, I hope it isn't anything serious. 
        Lady Lucaria: I don't care about the competitions, as long as he's okay.
        Roy: Aha! 
        Roy: I think Luxo here simply has an upset stomach. 
        Roy: Did you maybe eat something you shouldn't have?
        Luxo: Mwahhhhh...
        Roy: He'll be just fine in a few days. 
        Roy: If you give him this medicine I made, he should feel better almost immediately. 
        Lady Lucaria: You're both so kind to stop and help us. 
        Lady Lucaria: I don't know what we would have done, otherwise.
        Roy: ...
        Roy: Ah, no problem! 
        Roy: We must be away now. Please excuse us, my Lady.
        Lady Lucaria: Thank you both so much. 
        Lady Lucaria: It's been a pleasure meeting such a lovely couple. 
        Roy: Couple...?!
        Player: Your face is flushed, Roy! 
        Player: Are you feeling okay?
        Roy: Oh, I-I'm fine!
            -> Player: Maybe I should take your hand, just in case?
                <<set $Roy_Affection += 2>>
                Roy: Ah, erm, sure!
            -> Player: Give me your hand. I'll help walk you back.
                <<set $Roy_Affection += 1>>
                Roy: Actually, I do feel a bit light-headed. 
            Player: My heart is racing now too...
            Roy: There must definitely be something going around this ship, right {$playerName}?
            Player: Oh, erm... Definitely!
            Roy: And look at the time! 
            Roy: We'd better head back or you'll miss the next course. 
    -> Player: They're in a fancy suite. They'll have plenty of servants to help them, I'm sure.
        <<set $Roy_Affection -= 1>>
        Roy: Oh, well, if you say so...
        Roy: I hope they're alright in there...
        Roy: Oh and look at the time! 
        Roy: We'd better head back or you'll miss the next course.
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_Date_Sheila
tags:
---
Sheila: Eurgh, I'm so nervous! 
Sheila: I don't know what to say to her.
Player: Just be yourself. 
Player: Her fame, beauty or status doesn't make her anything more than another human being.
Sheila: Hehe, she's like a goddess to me! 
Sheila: But you're right. 
Sheila: I wonder if it's okay to ask for something from her.
Player: Like what?
Sheila: You know, like show tips or an autograph... 
Sheila: Gah! Are those too much? 
Sheila: I should play it cool.
    -> Player: Come on, we're gonna get them all!
        Sheila: We are? 
        Sheila: I mean, we are! 
        Sheila: Let's go!
        Lady Lucaria: Oh, hello! What a lovely pair of visitors! 
        Lady Lucaria: How can I help you both?
        Sheila: ...
        Sheila: I'm Sheila, your biggest fan ever, Lady Lucaria! 
        Player: I've come as her escort, my Lady.
        Lady Lucaria: It's wonderful to meet you. 
        Lady Lucaria: Oh, is that your Familiar, Sheila? How cute!
        Sheila: I'm planning on entering her in Crusts, just like your Luxo.
        Lady Lucaria: Is that so? 
        Lady Lucaria: I hope then that you'll be entering the Omen City contest. 
        Lady Lucaria: I'm going to be one of the judges there.
        Sheila: I sure am! 
        Lady Lucaria: Excellent. 
        Lady Lucaria: In that case, let me give you some show tips...
        Player: Sheila seems much more comfortable now. I'll leave her to it.
        Sheila: That was amazing! 
        Sheila: I feel like I know so many new things now that Mab and I can practise. 
        Sheila: Oh, and I got an autograph too!
        Player: That's great!
        Sheila: ...
        Sheila: Do you think I can be like her one day, {$playerName}?
            -> Player: I have complete faith in you and Mab.
                <<set $Sheila_Affection += 1>>
                Sheila: Really? 
                Sheila: I mean, it's true that we need to be more beautiful, more poised, more graceful. 
                Sheila: It's not impossible if we work hard.
            -> Player: You don't need to be more like her. 
                <<set $Sheila_Affection += 2>>
                Player: I'm sure you'd win just by being yourself.
                Sheila: You do flatter me, {$playerName}. 
                Sheila: But I know we still need to do some serious work on our beauty, poise and grace. 
            Sheila: I hope I'll get to see you cheer me on at the competition in Omen City. 
            Player: Of course I'll be there. 
            Player: And one day, when you're a Crusts winner, I want your autograph.
            Sheila: You bet! I'll give you as many as you want.
            Sheila: Gah! Have you seen the time? 
            Sheila: We'd better head back before we miss the next course. 
    -> Player: Ugh, all this fan-girling is making me cringe. 
        <<set $Sheila_Affection -= 1>>
        Player: You should just go in alone.
        Sheila: What? 
        Sheila: But I can't do this alone... 
        Sheila: Am I being too weird? 
        Sheila: Maybe I shouldn't go in after all.
        Sheila: I guess we're cutting it fine anyway...
        Sheila: We'd better head back before we miss the next course...
===

