title: chapter2_SSSpam_StopItMilitia_Damien_or_Eliza_PlayerWins_Roy_Activated
tags:
---
Grunt 1: Impossible!
Grunt 2: Inconceivable!
Regiment Leader: Damn it! 
Regiment Leader: I didn't expect you to be so strong. 
Regiment Leader: Quick, let's get out of here! 
Regiment Leader: Leave the Familiars!
Grunt 2: Run!
Grunt 1: Aaaah!
Regiment Leader: At least I left you with a small parting gift from me.
Player: Oh, I'm bleeding! 
Player: I must have got so caught up in the battle that I hadn't noticed their Familiar slash my leg.
Player: Ugh...
Player: I don't feel so good...
Roy: {$playerName}, you're awake!
Roy: How are you feeling?
Player: I'm alright, I think. 
Player: I injured my leg, right? 
Player: It doesn't hurt anymore. 
Player: What happened? 
Player: Did the StopIt! Militia kidnap any Familiars?
Roy: Thanks to you, the StopIt! Militia fled without a single Familiar in their clutches. 
Roy: Unfortunately, they did manage to escape but no one was harmed during their attack. 
Roy: Well... erm... apart from you. 
Roy: Thankfully, Seraph and I were able to heal your wound. 
Roy: But if your rescuer hadn't found you, it could have been much more serious.
Player: My rescuer?
Roy: Someone carried you to us and made sure you would be okay. 
Roy: They seemed very distressed. 
Player: What did they look like?
<<if $Damien_Activated == 1>> 
Roy: They ran off pretty quickly but I think they were male, with dark hair?
<<endif>>
<<if $Eliza_Activated == 1>> 
Roy: They ran off pretty quickly but I think they were female, with dark hair in a ponytail?
<<endif>>
    -> Player: Interesting.
    -> Player: (Say Nothing).
Roy: We're almost at Omen City port. 
Roy: You should rest up until we arrive.
<<if $Damien_Activated == 1>> 
Player: Damien saved me?
Player: How strange.
<<endif>>
<<if $Eliza_Activated == 1>> 
Player: Eliza saved me?
Player: How strange.
<<endif>>
===

