title: chapter3_OmenCity_PotionShop_Anne1
tags:
---
Anne: Why, hello there, {$playerName}! 
Anne: Boy, I am glad to see you back on dry land.
Player: Anne? 
Player: Is this your shop?
Anne: It is indeed. 
Anne: Golem and I finally made it back. 
Anne: Not sure how much longer I'll be here though. 
Anne: Money calls! 
Anne: My assistant, Clarice, is currently out doing an errand for me. 
Anne: Could you help me test a new potion while you're here?
    -> Player: Sure!
    Anne: You're a good sport, {$playerName}.
    Anne: Here. Open wide!
    Anne: Well? 
    Anne: Do you feel any different?
    Player: Not really...
    Anne: Hahahaha! 
    Anne: That colour change was unexpected! 
    Anne: Thank goodness it was temporary.
    Player: What was it supposed to do?
    Anne: It was supposed to make you feel warm, for colder climates like in the North. 
    Anne: I think perhaps the addition of blueberry pie crust was overdoing it. 
    Anne: I'll work more on that later. 
    Anne: Thanks, {$playerName}. 
    Anne: Here's a free healing potion for your troubles.
    -> Player: No Way.
    Player: Unless you promise to pay me compensation if something goes wrong?
    Anne: I appreciate your thrifty mindset, even if it is a bit boring.
===

