title: chapter3_OmenCity_FamiliarNursery_Sheila1
tags:
---
<<declare $cheer = 0>>
Head Breeder Minnie: And now, the final entrant to the first qualifier for the Royal Gantoh Crusts.
Head Breeder Minnie: Miss Sheila Feywin from Salt Mire City and her wind element Familiar, Queen Mab.
    -> Go Sheila! Go Queen Mab!
        <<set $Sheila_Affection += 1>>
        Head Breeder Minnie: Wow, well aren't these two popular!
        <<set $cheer = 1>>
    -> (Say nothing.)
        <<set $Sheila_Affection -= 1>>
        Head Breeder Minnie: ...
Head Breeder Minnie: Now, let's wait while the judges do their examination.
Head Breeder Minnie: Lady Lucaria, would you do the honours of revealing the rankings? 
Lady Lucaria: Of course. 
Head Breeder Minnie: Remember all, only the contestant who achieves first place will go through to the next qualifier at Arrowroot Town.
Lady Lucaria: In third place, we have the Familiar...
Lady Lucaria: ...
Lady Lucaria: Barnaby.
Crowd: *Applause.*
Lady Lucaria: In second place, we have the Familiar...
Lady Lucaria: ...
Lady Lucaria: Cookie.
Crowd: *Applause.*
Lady Lucaria: Which means, in first place...
Lady Lucaria: We have the Familiar Queen Mab, shown by Sheila! 
Lady Lucaria: Congratulations, my dear!
Crowd: *Applause.*
Sheila: ...
Sheila: I can't believe it. 
Sheila: We won! 
Sheila: We did it, Mab!
Queen Mab: Squeak!
<<if $cheer == 1>>
    Sheila: {$playerName}!
    Sheila: I'm so glad you're here. 
    Sheila: I heard you cheer for me. 
    Sheila: That means a whole lot to Mab and I. 
    Sheila: We're not very well known in showing circles yet.
        -> Player: It's no problem. 
            Player: You both deserved that win!
            Sheila: Thanks! 
            Sheila: You're obviously my good luck charm. Hehe!
        -> Player: Of course. Mab did great!
            Sheila: She did...
            Sheila: Although she did manage to bend her third left whisker while walking to the judges. 
            Sheila: That could have cost us the victory, Mab. 
            Sheila: You need to be more careful. 
            Sheila: At the later stages, they won't accept anything less than perfection!
<<endif>>
<<if $cheer == 0>>
    Sheila: {$playerName}!
    Sheila: Thanks for coming to watch me...
    Sheila: I wish more people had cheered. 
    Sheila: I thought you might, you know?
        -> Player: Sorry, I was nervous.
            Sheila: I get it. I was too.
        -> Player: No one else did.
            <<set $Sheila_Affection -= 1>>
            Sheila: Right...
            Sheila: It's because Mab bent her third left whisker while walking to the judges, wasn't it? 
            Sheila: Mab, I told you to be careful! 
            Sheila: You need to be perfect, do you hear? 
            Sheila: Perfect!
<<endif>>
===

title: chapter3_OmenCity_Harbour_Matthias1
tags:
---
Matthias: Hi, {$playerName}! 
Matthias: I'm glad you came. 
Matthias: I'm just about to take this little row boat out to a nearby cove. 
Matthias: If it's not too much trouble, would you like to come with me?
    -> Yeah. Lead the way!
        <<set $Matthias_Affection += 1>>
        Matthias: That's great! 
        Matthias: Don't worry, I'll do all the rowing.
        <<jump chapter3_OmenCity_Harbour_Matthias2>>
    -> Player: No thanks.
        <<set $Matthias_Affection -= 1>>
        Matthias: Oh...
        Matthias: Don't worry, I understand. 
        Matthias: Sorry to have bothered you, {$playerName}.
===

title: chapter3_OmenCity_Harbour_Matthias2
tags:
---
Matthias: You see these, {$playerName}? 
Matthias: These are ancient elvish carvings. 
Player: Are you interested in elvish history?
Matthias: Not really. 
Matthias: I wish this was a visit fuelled by curiosity, rather than necessity.
Matthias: You see, there have been some strange and dangerous weather patterns in some of the rivers and seas across Gantoh of late. 
Matthias: They suggest a sudden shift in the natural forces at play.
Matthias: It will take me some time to interpret these carvings. 
Matthias: What would you like to do?
    -> Player: I'll stay with you. 
        <<set $Matthias_Affection += 1>>
        Player: I want to learn more.
        Matthias: Here, come closer. 
        Matthias: If you wouldn't mind, of course. 
        Matthias: Let me show you what I'm looking for in particular...
        Matthias: These carvings refer to some special, legendary Familiars. 
        Matthias: According to the stories, they were usually ascended ones, Familiars that had grown in power and strength and taken a new form in doing so. 
        Matthias: They were used by the elves to help them control the elements, including the rivers and seas.
        Player: What happened to them after the elves disappeared?
        Matthias: In the myths and tales throughout history, they continued doing what they always had, for the most part. 
        Matthias: They were believed to help maintain the balance. 
        Matthias: There was apparently a legendary Familiar, this one here, whose territory covered this part of Gantoh and the seas around Salt Mire and Omen City.
        Player: What was their name?
        Matthias: Salix, the fabled Guardian of Gantoh's Sunset Waters.
        Player: If there has been a sudden change, do you think that means that...
            -> Player: The legendary Familiar abandoned its territory.
                Matthias: Surely that's not possible...
            -> Player: Something happened to the legendary Familiar.
                <<set $Matthias_Affection += 1>>
                Matthias: That is my current theory too.
            -> Player: The legendary Familiar never really existed.
                <<set $Matthias_Affection -= 1>>
                Matthias: No, I know that the stories are true! 
                Matthias: I mean, it's no big deal, ha ha! 
                Matthias: I'm sure lots of people think the same...
        Matthias: I was hoping to narrow down the possible locations of Salix's lair according to the myths and legends. 
        Matthias: Whilst these carvings confirm that the elves believed there was one, they don't give much else away...
        Matthias: I think I will have to try the library in Arrowroot Town. 
        Matthias: There might be some books or scrolls there that can help me find a place to search or...
        Matthias: Confirm that this was nothing more than a myth, after all.
        Matthias: Come on, let's head back for now. 
        Matthias: Thanks for coming with me, {$playerName}. 
        Matthias: You've been a great help. 
        Matthias: And pleasant company, as always!
    -> Player: I'll wait in the boat.
        Matthias: Of course...
        Matthias: I mean, yeah, this is pretty boring, right? 
        Matthias: Ha ha...
        Matthias: ...
        Matthias: I'm sorry. 
        Matthias: I won't be long.
===

title: chapter3_OmenCity_Harbour_Matthias3
tags:
---
Matthias: Omen City has a really quaint, mystical atmosphere to it, don't you think? 
Matthias: It's a little bit spooky too, ha ha!
===

title: chapter3_OmenCity_Alley_Kenny1
tags:
---
Player: Kenny?
Kenny: You! 
Kenny: How did you recognise me?
Player: What do you mean? 
Player: You're... you.
Kenny: Hmmm...
Kenny: You don't look like you're being deceitful. 
Kenny: Interesting.
Kenny: You seem to have a keen eye, anyway, {$playerName}. 
Kenny: Maybe you can be of use to me. 
Kenny: This is official business remember, so don't go spouting this all over Gantoh. 
Kenny: Do you understand?
    -> Player: Sure?
        Kenny: You could try to be a bit more convincing! 
    -> Player: Of course!
        Kenny: Ha! You're very keen, aren't you?
Kenny: I will keep some details classified, obviously. 
Kenny: Just in case you are a gossip.
Kenny: I am searching for a rather special Familiar that has gone missing, currently believed to be kidnapped by the StopIt! Militia. 
Kenny: I followed them here to Omen City. 
Kenny: Unfortunately, the trail has gone cold.
Kenny: If you hear of anything to do with a kidnapped Familiar or the StopIt! Militia, please tell me at once.
    -> Player: ...
        Kenny: ...
        Kenny: I'm on the clock.
        Kenny: Stop wasting my time.
    -> Player: Will do!
        Player: I'll keep my eyes open for you.
        Kenny: Report back if you catch wind of anything.
===

